events.description: Rebels sack the Chinese capital Chang'an during a peasant rebellion.
events.html: • AD 23 – Rebels sack the Chinese capital Chang'an during a peasant rebellion.

events.description: Otto IV is crowned Emperor of the Holy Roman Empire by Pope Innocent III.

events.description: The Byzantine–Venetian War comes to an end.
events.html: • 1302 – The Byzantine–Venetian War comes to an end.

events.description: Battle of Lake Poyang: In one of the largest naval battles in history, Zhu Yuanzhang's rebels defeat rival Chen Youliang.
events.html: • 1363 – Battle of Lake Poyang: In one of the largest naval battles in history, Zhu Yuanzhang's rebels defeat rival Chen Youliang.

events.description: Formation of the Holy League of Aragon, the Papal States and Venice against France.

events.description: The Coverdale Bible is printed, with translations into English by William Tyndale and Myles Coverdale.
events.html: • 1535 – The Coverdale Bible is printed, with translations into English by William Tyndale and Myles Coverdale.[2]

events.description: The Gregorian Calendar is introduced by Pope Gregory XIII.
events.html: • 1582 – The Gregorian Calendar is introduced by Pope Gregory XIII.

events.description: Governor Gonzalo Méndez de Canço begins to suppress a native uprising against his rule in what is now the US state of Georgia.
events.html: • 1597 – Governor Gonzalo Méndez de Canço begins to suppress a native uprising against his rule in what is now the US state of Georgia.

events.description: Eighty Years' War and the Anglo-Spanish War: A fleet of Spanish galleys are defeated by English and Dutch galleons in the English Channel.

events.description: Thirty Years' War: The Swedish Army defeats the armies of Saxony and the Holy Roman Empire at the Battle of Wittstock.

events.description: Nine Years' War: Piedmontese troops are defeated by the French.
events.html: • 1693 – Nine Years' War: Piedmontese troops are defeated by the French.

events.description: American Revolutionary War: Troops under George Washington are repelled by British troops under William Howe.
events.html: • 1777 – American Revolutionary War: Troops under George Washington are repelled by British troops under William Howe.

events.description: Napoleon first rises to prominence by suppressing counter-revolutionary rioters threatening the National Convention.
events.html: • 1795 – Napoleon first rises to prominence by suppressing counter-revolutionary rioters threatening the National Convention.

events.description: Mexico adopts a new constitution and becomes a federal republic.
events.html: • 1824 – Mexico adopts a new constitution and becomes a federal republic.

events.description: The Belgian Revolution takes legal form when the provisional government secedes from the Netherlands.
events.html: • 1830 – The Belgian Revolution takes legal form when the provisional government secedes from the Netherlands.

events.description: The Crimean War begins when the Ottoman Empire declares war on the Russian Empire.
events.html: • 1853 – The Crimean War begins when the Ottoman Empire declares war on the Russian Empire.

events.description: The Agricultural and Mechanical College of Texas opens as the first public college in Texas.
events.html: • 1876 – The Agricultural and Mechanical College of Texas opens as the first public college in Texas.

events.description: First run of the Orient Express.

events.description: First meeting of the Boys' Brigade in Glasgow, Scotland.

events.description: World War I: The Battle of Broodseinde is fought between the British and German armies in Flanders.

events.description: The Mannerheim League for Child Welfare, a Finnish non-governmental organization, is founded on the initiative of Sophie Mannerheim.

events.description: The Metropolitan Police and various anti-fascist organizations violently clash in the Battle of Cable Street.
